<body>
    <h1>eZ Publish Cloud -Beta- Whitelist</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"eZPublishCloud-Beta-Whitelist-SupportedeZPublishfeaturesintheClou=
d-Whitelist(+potentialBlacklistitems)">Supported eZ Publish features in the=
 Cloud - Whitelist (+potential Blacklist items)</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>This document describes the eZ Publish features/environments and customi=
zations supported by the cloud. Anything not mentioned in this doc is by de=
fault not supported.&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3 id=3D"eZPublishCloud-Beta-Whitelist-eZPublish5.1LS[1]">eZ Publish 5.1 L=
S<a href=3D"#_ftn1" name=3D"_ftnref1" rel=3D"nofollow"></a>[1]&nbsp;</h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span style=3D"font-size: 11.0pt;font=
-family: Arial , sans-serif;font-style: normal;"><br /></span></span></p>
<ol>
<li>eZ Publish 5.1.0 out-of-the-box, no kernel hacks or changes (except for=
 any service packs). This also implies no kernel overrides</li>
<li>eZ Publish in virtual host mode (standard eZ Publish5.1 LS rewrite rule=
s)<br />
<ol>
<li>Custom apache rewriterules must be specified in eZ Cloud extension - if=
 any</li>
<li>HostMatch setting in <code>site.ini</code> must contain all production =
hostnames (=E2=80=9Clocalhost=E2=80=9D or any non-unique names not allowed)=
</li>
</ol></li>
<li>eZ Publish uploaded to cloud must be configured for single mode (once u=
ploaded to the cloud, the installation will run in eZDFS cluster mode)<br /=
>
<ol>
<li>Since site is running in cluster mode, there are a few things in the ad=
min interface which cannot be used as they are not cluster aware. This incl=
udes (but is not limited to)<br />
<ol>
<li>Packages management</li>
<li>Ini editor</li>
</ol></li>
</ol></li>
<li>Extensions
<ol>
<li>Extension located in extension/ is supported</li>
<li>Since the site is running in cluster mode, custom extensions needs to b=
e cluster aware.<br />
<ol>
<li>Do for instance not save files on local file system and expect it to be=
 available on all webservers</li>
</ol></li>
<li>Also, all templates and designs must be located in an extension (not in=
 [docroot]/design/)</li>
<li>Extensions must be designed to be able to work without the need for any=
 daemons, scripts etc.</li>
<li>Notes regarding Official extensions:
<ol>
<li>Open office is not running as daemon in the environment, so imports pro=
vided by the <code>ezodf</code> extensions which depends on the daemon is n=
ot supported ( like .doc and .pdf imports ).</li>
<li>ezodoscope extension is not supported</li>
<li>ezoracle is not supported.</li>
<li>eznetwork is not supported. Instead, patches are available for installa=
tion using the Cloud administration interface.</li>
<li>ezrecommendation extension is not supported</li>
<li>ezcontentstaging is not supported. But eZ Publish Cloud has a built-in =
staging functionality. However, this build-in staging functionality is diff=
erent than the one provided by ezcontentstaging</li>
<li>ezxmlexport is not supported. This extension is not cluster aware, and =
no functionality is available for extracting the exported files from the cl=
oud</li>
</ol></li>
</ol></li>
<li>eZ Publish must be configured in host-matching mode (uri based and othe=
rs not supported)</li>
<li>eZ Find is supported, however only with default one-core setup (no mult=
ilingual)<br />
<ol>
<li>We support custom solr configs on request (needs review)<br />
<ol>
<li>Custom config tarball (<code>schema.xml</code>, <code>protwords.txt</co=
de>, <code>stopwords.txt</code>, <code>synonyms.txt</code>) to be uploaded =
to ftp and must be specified in <code>ezcloud</code> extension.</li>
</ol></li>
<li>Custom solr configs must be reviewed and approved by eZ Cloud team in a=
dvance. Requests might be declined due to security or technical constraints=
</li>
</ol></li>
<li>Only MySQL 5.1 is supported<br />
<ol>
<li>Postgresql and oracle is not supported</li>
</ol></li>
<li>Single database installation (using one database connection for all sit=
eaccesses)<br />
<ol>
<li>As a side effect, eZ Content Staging is not supported in the cloud</li>
</ol></li>
<li>Custom Database tables are supported (as long as they are in the same D=
B)</li>
<li>No database GUI available (only complete DB imports and exports are pos=
sible)</li>
<li>Only PHP 5.3 supported<br />
<ol>
<li>Encrypted phar package files are not supported as there is a bug with R=
HEL=E2=80=99s version of PHP 5.3</li>
<li>The following PHP extensions are supported:<br />
<ol>
<li>apc</li>
<li>bz2</li>
<li>calendar</li>
<li>Core</li>
<li>ctype</li>
<li>curl</li>
<li>date</li>
<li>dom</li>
<li>ereg</li>
<li>exif</li>
<li>fileinfo</li>
<li>filter</li>
<li>ftp</li>
<li>gd</li>
<li>gettext</li>
<li>gmp</li>
<li>hash</li>
<li>iconv</li>
<li>json</li>
<li>libxml</li>
<li>mbstring</li>
<li>mcrypt</li>
<li>mongo</li>
<li>mysql</li>
<li>mysqli</li>
<li>openssl</li>
<li>pcntl</li>
<li>pcre</li>
<li>PDO</li>
<li>pdo_mysql</li>
<li>Phar</li>
<li>posix</li>
<li>readline</li>
<li>Reflection</li>
<li>session</li>
<li>shmop</li>
<li>SimpleXML</li>
<li>soap</li>
<li>sockets</li>
<li>SPL</li>
<li>sqlite3</li>
<li>standard</li>
<li>suhosin</li>
<li>sysvmsg</li>
<li>sysvsem</li>
<li>sysvshm</li>
<li>tokenizer</li>
<li>xml</li>
<li>xmlreader</li>
<li>xmlwriter</li>
<li>xsl</li>
<li>zlib</li>
</ol></li>
</ol></li>
<li>Cronjobs must be specified in <code>ezcloud</code> extension</li>
<li>Mail settings using SMTP (configured automatically, any custom settings=
 will be overridden)</li>
<li>Only <code>http</code> and <code>https</code> outgoing traffic is allow=
ed and must be opened server-side by Ixonos<strong> [2]</strong><br />
<ol>
<li>List of hostnames / ip must be provided by client</li>
<li>Wildcards (access to anywhere) not allowed</li>
</ol></li>
<li>CDN : not supported at the moment</li>
<li>Site will run behind Varnish<br />
<ol>
<li>Varnish configuration is fixed (cannot be changed by customer)</li>
<li>Non-logged-in users in live sites will be served by varnish</li>
</ol></li>
<li>Shell access is not available<br />
<ol>
<li>No scripts can be executed from command</li>
</ol></li>
<li>Access and error logs are not available</li>
<li><code>Http</code> supported, <code>https</code> not supported</li>
<li>Sites uploaded to the eZ Cloud must work with eZ Publish=E2=80=99 cache=
s enabled. This includes (but is not limited to):<br />
<ol>
<li>View cache</li>
<li>Template cache</li>
<li>Role cache</li>
<li>Policy cache</li>
<li>Design location cache</li>
<li>Translation cache</li>
<li>Template compile</li>
<li>Template optimization</li>
<li>Development mode is disabled</li>
<li>Override cache</li>
</ol></li>
<li>Settings which be automatically disabled in the cloud<br />
<ol>
<li>SQL debug</li>
<li>Redirection debug</li>
<li>Debug output</li>
<li>Regional settings debug</li>
<li>Template debug</li>
</ol></li>
<li>Http /php settings<br />
<ol>
<li><code>upload_max_file =3D 100Mb</code></li>
<li><code>post_max_size =3D 100Mb</code></li>
<li><code>max_execution_time =3D 120</code></li>
<li><code>memory_limit =3D 128Mb</code></li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h5 id=3D"eZPublishCloud-Beta-Whitelist-Glossary">Glossary</h5>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoFootnoteText"><strong>[1]</strong> - At the moment eZ Publis=
h 4.7 is also supported, but support for this version will be replaced by 5=
.1 LS.</p>
<p class=3D"MsoFootnoteText">&quot;<strong>5.1 LS</strong>&quot; - refers t=
o Legacy Stack (no symfony stack)</p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoFootnoteText"><a href=3D"#_ftnref2" name=3D"_ftn2" rel=3D"no=
follow"></a><strong>[2]</strong> - Not supported at the time of writing, bu=
t will be some time in the future</p>
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
    </div>
